sentence: Futures tied to the S&P 500 were little changed on Wednesday after bleak consumer confidence data provided a sobering view on the health of the economy, while investors held back ahead of Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell's speech this week.
ET, Dow e-minis 1YMc1 were down 0.16% at 28,148.
S&P 500 e-minis ESc1 were up 0.03% at 3,444, while Nasdaq 100 e-minis NQc1 were up 0.37% at 11,769.25.
